  "target_response": {
    "text": "You can get a decent read without any score by watching a few low-tech signals. Sleep is the one you already track: last night you logged 398 minutes, about 6.6 hours, which is on the short side, so treat today as a day to be honest about effort. Beyond duration, the reliable everyday markers are morning mood and motivation, muscle soreness that's fading versus lingering, appetite, and how the first ten minutes of a warm-up feel; legs that come around quickly usually mean you're recovered. Since your entries are manual, treat the numbers as approximate. A practical upgrade that costs nothing: add a one-to-five morning freshness rating next to each sleep entry. After a couple of weeks, that pair tells you most of what a recovery score would.",
